Sinotex of China, Cotton Co. of Zimbabwe Agree Seeds Deal, Herald Reports

-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 
2011-03-07T07:02:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/sinotex-of-china-cotton-co-of-zimbabwe-in-seeds-deal-herald-reports.html
  Sinotex Investment & Development (600061)  Co.
and the Cotton Co. of  Zimbabwe  agreed a $500 million deal to
finance the production and purchase of seed cotton, the Herald
reported, citing unidentified sources.  The deal will be financed by the China Development Bank
Corp., which also provided $10 million for the purchase of
cotton lint by Sinotex from Cottco, the Harare-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  